
[1]summons

   SUM'MONS, n. with a plural termination, but used in the singular
   number; as a summons is prepared. [L. submoneas.]

   A call by authority or the command of a superior to appear at a place
   named, or to attend to some public duty.

   This summons he resolved not to disobey.

   He sent to summon the seditious and to offer pardon; but neither
   summons nor pardon was regarded.

   1. In law, a warning or citation to appear in court; or a written
   notification signed by the proper officer, to be served on a person,
   warning him to appear in court at a day specified, to answer to the
   demand of the plaintiff.
